    //       "description": "<p>Working hours – Full time (32-40h)</p>\n<p>As an ambitious and technically advanced company, we are always innovating and moving forward. We are currently looking for an experienced Product Owner who can help our R&amp;D software team to reach the next level and create even better-quality products.</p>\n<p>Does this sound like a challenge to you? Then, keep on reading!</p>\n<p>What will you be doing?</p>\n<p>As Product Owner, you will be working closely with software engineers and other R&amp;D disciplines in a multidisciplinary way to take owners of product innovation and engineering: translate abstract requirements into tangible solutions and realize the required progress (Quality, Time, Functionality and Costs) together with your (software) team. You feel accountable for your own part but also responsible for the whole printer.</p>\n<p>Do you fit this profile?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Technical University Master’s degree in in Computer Science, Physics, Data Sciences, Mechatronics, Informatics, or equivalent</li>\n<li>Experience with real-time embedded software and at least two of the following programming languages: Python, QT, C++ and C</li>\n<li>Experience with architecting and designing (embedded) software</li>\n<li>Experience with Scrum/agile methodologies</li>\n<li>Affiliation with electronics, mechanics and 3D printing</li>\n<li>Ability to deal adequately with unexpected work situations</li>\n<li>Ability to keep high quality standards also under work pressure</li>\n<li>A proactive, passionate, inventive team player</li>\n<li>Excellent communication skills in English</li>\n<li>An inspiring motivation letter covering the profile requirements</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Definitely a plus</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience with JIRA and GitHub</li>\n<li>Experience with 3D printing (FDM)</li>\n<li>Ambition to grow to an architect, team lead, product owner or product lead</li>\n<li>Very good communication skills in Dutch</li>\n<li>Relevant R&amp;D experience</li>\n<li>You are a certified product owner</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The benefits of working with us</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A competitive salary in line with your experience</li>\n<li>Ultimaker makes contributions to your pension</li>\n<li>We pay for your daily commute based on public transport</li>\n<li>27 days of paid leave per year</li>\n<li>Use of an Ultimaker 3D printer</li>\n<li>An open, family atmosphere, and a fun work environment</li>\n<li>Work in a young and energetic team</li>\n<li>Lunch with healthy sandwiches, salads and a daily special</li>\n<li>A convenient location within walking distance of public transport and near the highway</li>\n<li>Room to expand your knowledge by following courses and going to meetups</li>\n</ul>\n<p>More detail about Ultimaker</p>\n<p>Ultimaker has been in operation since 2011, and over the years has grown to become a market leader, creating powerful, professional, and accessible desktop 3D printers. With offices in the Netherlands, New York, Boston, and Singapore, plus production facilities in Europe and the US, Ultimaker’s team of more than 400 employees continually strives to accelerate the world’s transition to local digital manufacturing by offering the highest-quality 3D printers, software, and materials on the market.</p>\n<p>We offer you the chance to become a part of a young, fast-growing, technically advanced company. We are focused on further developing the Ultimaker, developing the world of 3D printing, and further expanding the skills of our people.\nWe are ordinary people with extraordinary plans. Creating high-quality products is our driver. Our passion and creativity help us to make the unbelievable believable. Together, we make one hell of a team.</p>\n<p>Check out on our blog: ultimaker.com/learn/blog</p>\n<p>Find us on YouTube: youtube.com/channel/UCGEx6-kWhUwmwJOih_R2wUQ</p>\n",
